Classes
Class
Description
Board
Represents the game board for the Jungle King game.
Cat
The Cat class represents a Cat piece in the game extended from Piece.
Dog
The Dog class represents a Dog piece in the game and extended from Piece
Elephant
The Elephant class represents an Elephant piece in the game.
GameController
The GameController class manages user input and game interactions for the game.
GameModel
The GameModel class handles the game's logic Manages the board, turns, movement of pieces, and determining the winner.
GameView
GameView class is the graphical user interface (GUI) for the game has visual elements for the game board, move history, and user interaction with the game including button clicks and updating the interface based on the game
HowToPlay
A class representing the "How to Play" screen of the game.
Lake
Represents a lake on the board
Leopard
Represents a Leopard piece in the game.
Lion
Represents a Lion piece in the game.
MenuScreen
Represents the menu screen for the game.
MusicPlayer
A class that plays background music in a loop.
Piece
Represents a piece in the game.
Player
Represents a player in the game.
PreGame
The PreGame class represents the player setup screen for the Jungle King game.
Rat
Represents a Rat piece in the game The Rat is being able to enter lakes and has special capture rules: - A rat in a lake can only capture another rat in a lake - A rat in a lake cannot capture land pieces - A rat on land follows normal capture rules
Square
Represents a square on the board
Terrain
Represents a terrain type on the board
Tiger
Represents the Tiger piece in the game, inheriting from the Piece class.
TitleScreen
Represents the title screen of the Jungle King game.
Trap
Represents a trap on the board
Wolf
Represents the Wolf piece in the Jungle King game.
